message.entry: An Access Token or API Key with the appropriate read/write permissions is required for read or write operations with Google Sheets. Ensure the correct permissions are set.
提供的 'Sheet' 值不是有效的工作表索引。有效的工作表索引必须为小于或等于指定工作簿中工作表数量的正整数。
Resource not found.
[内部]: 对于 Google Sheets，''matlab.io.spreadsheet.internal.createWorkbook'' 的第二个输入 ''文件名'' 不能为空。
An internal error has occurred while communicating with the Google Sheets server. Cause: ''{0}''
The range must be a character vector or string of the form ''A1:B2'' or ''A1''.
Unable to determine range. Range must be a named range in the sheet, or a single cell that cannot exceed 18278 as the column index and cannot exceed 10 million cells.
Cannot delete all the sheets from a Google Spreadsheet. A Google Spreadsheet must contain at least one sheet.
''MergedCellColumnRule'' and ''MergedCellRowRule'' are not supported for Google Sheets.
Google Sheet with spreadsheetId ''{0}'' not found.
[INTERNAL]: Loading an entire Google spreadsheet or pre-selecting the date and number formats for the entire workbook are not supported operations.
The input data exceeds the range for Google Sheets. A Google Spreadsheet cannot exceed 10 million cells or 18278 columns.
Request to the Google Sheets server timed out. Check the URL of the Google Sheet, the bandwidth of the internet connection, and the firewall settings.
The Google Sheets service is currently unavailable. Cause: ''{0}''
一个 Google Spreadsheet 不能包含多个具有相同标题的工作表。请使用 ''SheetTitles'' 名称-值参量提供一组唯一工作表标题。
Google Spreadsheet title cannot exceed 10000 characters.
The supplied URL ''{0}'' does not contain a valid Google spreadsheetId.
The Google Sheets server is currently limiting the number of requests that can be submitted per minute. Try again in a few minutes.
一个 Google Spreadsheet 不能包含多于 384 个工作表，因为这将超出 Google Spreadsheet 中 1000 万个单元格的最大限制。
A Google sheet must contain only tabular data. Google Sheets consisting of objects such as charts and images are not supported.
Input with spreadsheetId ''{0}'' is not a Google spreadsheet. Microsoft Excel spreadsheets have to be converted to Google Sheets for reading or writing.
''UseExcel'' cannot be used when reading or writing from Google sheets.
The range violates Google Sheets limits. Start and end boundaries must be positive, with a maximum of 18278 columns and a total area not exceeding 10 million cells.

The input data exceeds ~2MB size limit that Google Sheets allows for a single write operation. To resolve this issue, consider calling write in a loop on data that is split into smaller chunks using ''WriteMode=append''.
The range exceeds size limit supported for a single read operation. To resolve this issue, consider calling read in a loop with ''Range''.
The supplied URL ''{0}'' is an unsupported Google Sheet URL generated via "Publish To The Web".
